article.description: Cory Gensler posted 17 points and eight rebounds as Campbell romped past Hampton 75-49 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Gensler scores 17 to lift Campbell past Hampton 75-49
article.linkText: Gensler scores 17 to lift Campbell past Hampton 75-49
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Cory Gensler posted 17 points and eight rebounds as Campbell romped past Hampton 75-49 on Thursday night. Austin McCullough had 10 points for Campbell (13-13, 4-10 Big South Conference) as did Messiah Thompson. Joshua Lusane had three blocks. Jermaine Marrow had 22 points for the Pirates (11-14, 6-6). Ben Stanley added 15 points. Edward Greg Heckstall had a game-high nine rebounds. The Fighting Camels evened the season series against the Pirates with the win. Hampton defeated Campbell 83-74 on Jan. 23. Campbell plays Radford at home on Saturday. Hampton plays Longwood on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
